---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const calendarUrl = "https://calendar.google.com/calendar/u/0/appointments/schedules/AcZssZ2VXsiZVbhgdnhV1tkQ9J6N-roCQlSd4CDDA5BHEcf36xdz-4OJSNM_56LSe5vDu9G6-AZRXkCj";
---

<BaseLayout title="How AgentQ Works — Developer Assist | AgentQ" description="AI agents build your software. Real developers make sure it's ready to launch. You own everything.">

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       PAGE HEADER
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="pt-24 pb-12 md:pt-32 md:pb-16">
    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-5 md:px-10">
      <h1 class="type-display text-warm-black mb-4 max-w-[768px]">How AgentQ&nbsp;works.</h1>
      <p class="type-h3 text-warm-mid max-w-[672px]">AI agents build your software. Real developers make sure it's ready to launch. You own&nbsp;everything.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION 1: THE FULL JOURNEY
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 fade-in-section" aria-labelledby="journey-heading">
    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-5 md:px-10">
      <h2 id="journey-heading" class="type-h2 text-warm-black mb-12">From your idea to a launched&nbsp;product.</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
        <div class="card">
          <span class="type-overline text-stone mb-3 block">Step 1</span>
          <h3 class="type-h4 mb-2">You describe what your business&nbsp;needs.</h3>
          <p class="type-body text-warm-mid">Tell AgentQ what you're trying to solve. A client portal, a booking system, a marketplace, an internal tool. AgentQ's PM agent works with you to turn that into a clear build plan before a single line of code is&nbsp;written.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <span class="type-overline text-stone mb-3 block">Step 2</span>
          <h3 class="type-h4 mb-2">AI agents build&nbsp;it.</h3>
          <p class="type-body text-warm-mid">A team of specialized AI agents gets to work. Backend developer designs your database and APIs. Frontend developer builds the UI. Code auditor reviews every&nbsp;line.</p>
        </div>
        <!-- Step 3 stands out -->
        <div class="card" style="background: var(--color-forest); border: 1.5px solid var(--color-warm-black);">
          <span class="type-overline text-white/70 mb-3 block">Step 3</span>
          <h3 class="type-h4 mb-2 text-white">Real developers when you need&nbsp;them.</h3>
          <p class="type-body text-white/80">Hit a wall? Have a question? Want a human to check things over? Submit a request through Developer Assist. Real engineers who can see your project and give you specific&nbsp;answers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <span class="type-overline text-stone mb-3 block">Step 4</span>
          <h3 class="type-h4 mb-2">You&nbsp;launch.</h3>
          <p class="type-body text-warm-mid">One-click deployment. Dedicated database. Enterprise security. Clean code you own completely. Live in&nbsp;days.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION 2: DEVELOPER ASSIST DEEP DIVE
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 fade-in-section" aria-labelledby="devassist-deep-heading">
    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-5 md:px-10">
      <h2 id="devassist-deep-heading" class="type-h2 text-warm-black mb-4 max-w-[672px]">A real developer in your corner. From day&nbsp;one.</h2>
      <p class="type-body-lg text-warm-mid mb-10 max-w-[768px]">Every AgentQ plan includes Developer Assist. Real engineers who can see your project, understand your codebase, and give you specific answers to your specific&nbsp;situation.</p>
      <p class="type-body text-warm-mid mb-10 max-w-[768px]">You submit requests through your AgentQ dashboard. A developer reviews your project and responds. The fix gets applied, the question gets answered, you keep&nbsp;moving.</p>

      <!-- Placeholder for ticket system screenshot -->
      <div class="image-placeholder">
        <p class="type-body-sm text-stone">Developer Assist ticket interface screenshot</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION 3: WHAT DEV ASSIST COVERS
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 fade-in-section" aria-labelledby="covers-heading">
    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-5 md:px-10">
      <h2 id="covers-heading" class="type-h2 text-warm-black mb-10">From "what should I build" to "it's&nbsp;live."</h2>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="type-h4 mb-2">Figuring out what to&nbsp;build.</h3>
          <p class="type-body text-warm-mid mb-4">You know your business problem. You may not know what the software solution should look like. Developers help you think through the right approach before anything gets&nbsp;built.</p>
          <p class="type-body-sm text-stone italic">"I run a coaching institute with 3 branches. Students keep falling through the cracks because everything runs on WhatsApp. I need something better but I don't know where to&nbsp;start."</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="type-h4 mb-2">Solving for your business&nbsp;outcomes.</h3>
          <p class="type-body text-warm-mid mb-4">Developer Assist goes beyond fixing code. Developers help you connect what you're building to the business outcomes you care about. More efficient operations. Better customer&nbsp;experience.</p>
          <p class="type-body-sm text-stone italic">"We want to reduce the time our dispatch team spends assigning jobs from 2 hours a day to 15 minutes. What's the right way to build the scheduling&nbsp;logic?"</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="type-h4 mb-2">Architecture and&nbsp;planning.</h3>
          <p class="type-body text-warm-mid mb-4">How should your app be structured so it works as your business grows? Developers help with system design, database structure, and the decisions that feel invisible now but become expensive if they're&nbsp;wrong.</p>
          <p class="type-body-sm text-stone italic">"We're launching with 50 customers but we expect to grow to 500 this year. Will what we're building now handle&nbsp;that?"</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="type-h4 mb-2">Integrations.</h3>
          <p class="type-body text-warm-mid mb-4">Connecting payment gateways, CRMs, analytics tools, or any third-party service. If the service you need has an API, the team helps you connect&nbsp;it.</p>
          <p class="type-body-sm text-stone italic">"I need Razorpay for payments in India and Stripe for international customers. Can the system automatically route to the right&nbsp;one?"</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="type-h4 mb-2">Code review and&nbsp;security.</h3>
          <p class="type-body text-warm-mid mb-4">Before you go live, a developer reviews the code, checks for security gaps, and makes sure the app is solid enough for real customers with real&nbsp;data.</p>
          <p class="type-body-sm text-stone italic">"We're about to launch and I want someone experienced to check everything over before my first paying customers use&nbsp;it."</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="type-h4 mb-2">Getting&nbsp;unstuck.</h3>
          <p class="type-body text-warm-mid mb-4">The AI produced something that's not working. Or you've hit a wall and don't know what to do next. Describe the problem. A developer figures it&nbsp;out.</p>
          <p class="type-body-sm text-stone italic">"I've been going back and forth with the AI on the login flow for two days and it's still not right. I need a human to look at&nbsp;this."</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="type-h4 mb-2">Deployment and&nbsp;launch.</h3>
          <p class="type-body text-warm-mid mb-4">Getting your app live. A developer verifies everything works. You launch with&nbsp;confidence.</p>
          <p class="type-body-sm text-stone italic">"Everything looks ready. I want someone to do a final check before I send this to&nbsp;customers."</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION 4: THE TIERS
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 fade-in-section" aria-labelledby="tiers-heading">
    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-5 md:px-10">
      <h2 id="tiers-heading" class="type-h2 text-warm-black mb-10">Support that scales with&nbsp;you.</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-8">
        <div class="tier-card">
          <p class="type-overline text-stone mb-3">Standard</p>
          <h3 class="type-h4 mb-2">On-demand developer support.</h3>
          <p class="type-body text-warm-mid mb-4">Submit requests through your dashboard. Get help with bugs, integrations, architecture decisions, and code review. Responses from experienced developers who can see your&nbsp;project.</p>
          <p class="type-body-sm text-stone">Best for founders building their first product or small business owners launching a custom&nbsp;tool.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tier-card-featured tier-card">
          <p class="type-overline text-forest mb-3">Priority</p>
          <h3 class="type-h4 mb-2">Faster response. Direct senior access.</h3>
          <p class="type-body mb-4" style="color: var(--color-stone);">Everything in Standard, with faster turnaround and direct access to senior developers. For projects where delays cost you customers or&nbsp;revenue.</p>
          <p class="type-body-sm" style="color: var(--color-warm-mid);">Best for founders in production with real users and real&nbsp;transactions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tier-card">
          <p class="type-overline text-stone mb-3">Enterprise</p>
          <h3 class="type-h4 mb-2">Solutions architects from the ground&nbsp;up.</h3>
          <p class="type-body text-warm-mid mb-4">Dedicated solutions architects who help with requirement gathering, scoping, and building complex systems. Involved from the start, not just when things&nbsp;break.</p>
          <p class="type-body-sm text-stone">Best for growing businesses with complex operational&nbsp;needs.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <a href="/pricing" class="type-body font-medium text-forest hover:text-forest-hover transition-colors">
        See pricing <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION 5: WHY WE BUILT THIS
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 fade-in-section" aria-labelledby="why-heading">
    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-5 md:px-10">
      <h2 id="why-heading" class="type-h2 text-warm-black mb-6">We read the data. Then we built the&nbsp;team.</h2>
      <div class="max-w-[768px]">
        <p class="type-body text-warm-mid mb-4">We evaluated six AI coding platforms across 68 metrics. The finding was clear: no platform scores above 60% on engineering quality. Every platform produces software that needs human involvement to reach production. Every single one. Including&nbsp;AgentQ.</p>
        <p class="type-body text-warm-mid mb-4">The difference is what you do about that gap. Most platforms leave it for you to figure&nbsp;out.</p>
        <p class="type-body text-warm-mid mb-6">AgentQ's gap is the smallest of any platform tested. 12 hours to production-ready, compared to 26 for the next closest and 60 for the worst. We built Developer Assist to handle those 12 hours for you. Because even the smallest gap still needs closing, and you shouldn't have to learn to code to close&nbsp;it.</p>
        <a href="/evals" class="type-body font-medium text-forest hover:text-forest-hover transition-colors">
          See the full evaluation <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION 6: WHAT TO EXPECT
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 fade-in-section" aria-labelledby="expect-heading">
    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-5 md:px-10">
      <h2 id="expect-heading" class="type-h2 text-warm-black mb-10">Clear on what this&nbsp;is.</h2>

      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-10">
        <!-- Left: What it is -->
        <div>
          <h3 class="section-label text-warm-mid mb-5">Developer Assist is:</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3 type-body">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-forest shrink-0 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <span>Real engineers who can read your code and understand your project</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-forest shrink-0 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <span>On-demand support built into every plan, not an add-on</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-forest shrink-0 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <span>Ongoing access for as long as you're building and maintaining your product</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-forest shrink-0 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <span>A team that works alongside you and the AI agents</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-forest shrink-0 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <span>Help with business decisions, not just technical ones</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Right: Common questions -->
        <div>
          <h3 class="section-label text-warm-mid mb-5">Common questions:</h3>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div>
              <p class="type-body font-medium text-warm-black">"Do I need to manage the developers?"</p>
              <p class="type-body text-warm-mid">No. Submit a request. Get a response. That's&nbsp;it.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="type-body font-medium text-warm-black">"Is this a chatbot?"</p>
              <p class="type-body text-warm-mid">No. Real people. They can see your project and give you specific&nbsp;answers.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="type-body font-medium text-warm-black">"Do I get the same developer every time?"</p>
              <p class="type-body text-warm-mid">On Priority and Enterprise tiers, you work with a consistent team who knows your&nbsp;project.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="type-body font-medium text-warm-black">"What if I need help at 2 AM?"</p>
              <p class="type-body text-warm-mid">Requests are handled during business hours. Enterprise plans include extended support&nbsp;windows.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION 7: CTA
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 fade-in-section">
    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-5 md:px-10">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_1fr] items-center" style="border: 1.5px solid var(--color-warm-black); border-radius: var(--radius-card); overflow: hidden;">
        <div style="padding: 40px;">
          <h2 class="type-h2 text-warm-black mb-4">Build with a team behind&nbsp;you.</h2>
          <p class="type-body-lg text-warm-mid mb-8 max-w-[576px]">Every plan includes Developer Assist. Real developers. Your project. No extra&nbsp;cost.</p>
          <a href={calendarUrl} class="btn-primary text-lg">
            Book a launch call <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
          </a>
        </div>
        <div class="hidden lg:block h-full">
          <img src="/images/cta.png" alt="" class="w-full h-full object-cover" style="transform: scaleX(-1);">
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
